
The program produces the energy spectra (saved then in data/sumData.root)
and the total livetimes for each run (saved then in data/sumData.dat) of
the 40 detectors installed in Gerda given a set of runIDs.

USAGE:
  ./processData [OPTIONS]

There must be a file named 'paths.txt' in the same location of
the executable formatted as the following:

  /path/to/gerda-metadata
  /path/to/data/structure
  /path/to/runconfiguration_mod.db
  runID1
  runID2
  ...
  runIDn

OPTIONS:

  --verbose : allow verbosity
  --help    : display this help message and return

ASSIGNABLE:

  --energy  : default is "gauss", specify "ZAC" to use energy
              reconstructed with the ZAC filter
              
              
